<div id="review_1393349637" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1393349637" />
    <a title="Jane Gregg" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30106888-jane-gregg"><img alt="Jane Gregg" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396150775p2/30106888.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1393349637?book_show_action=true">Sep 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jane Gregg" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jane Gregg" href="/user/show/30106888-jane-gregg">Jane Gregg</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1393349637" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14420964324349063212">Booze, pills, sex with a side order of violence? Don&apos;t mind if I do! This cautionary tale reveals the inner mind of the addict but does so in a way that is compelling without being preachy. Impossible you say? You&apos;d think so, but JA Wright manages to wave a deft hand across this narrative and bring us both the life and the soul of protagonist, Randall, without falling into schmaltz or clinical notes. Humour abounds as we look through the eyes of the young girl growing up in the fertile soil of a</span>
  <span id="freeText14420964324349063212" style="display:none">Booze, pills, sex with a side order of violence? Don't mind if I do! This cautionary tale reveals the inner mind of the addict but does so in a way that is compelling without being preachy. Impossible you say? You'd think so, but JA Wright manages to wave a deft hand across this narrative and bring us both the life and the soul of protagonist, Randall, without falling into schmaltz or clinical notes. Humour abounds as we look through the eyes of the young girl growing up in the fertile soil of adult addiction. What could have been a depressing read is ultimately hilarious in places, engaging and uplifting. One of the best of 2015.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14420964324349063212" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
