<div id="review_1353238628" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1353238628" />
    <a title="lindsay" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28839361-lindsay"><img alt="lindsay" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396955710p2/28839361.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1353238628?book_show_action=true">Aug 03, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="lindsay" class="user" itemprop="url" name="lindsay" href="/user/show/28839361-lindsay">lindsay</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1353238628" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4679369101087781516">I was lucky enough to receive an advanced copy of &apos;How to Grow an Addict&apos; by JA Wright, and I could not put it down! The prologue sets the scene with the main character entering rehab and being asked by her counselor what &apos;three things&apos; led her to become an addict. For the protagonist narrowing it down to just three things is the hard part and from there we are taken on a journey that delves into the repercussions of being raised by dysfunctional and emotionally unavailable parents, and the ways</span>
  <span id="freeText4679369101087781516" style="display:none">I was lucky enough to receive an advanced copy of 'How to Grow an Addict' by JA Wright, and I could not put it down! The prologue sets the scene with the main character entering rehab and being asked by her counselor what 'three things' led her to become an addict. For the protagonist narrowing it down to just three things is the hard part and from there we are taken on a journey that delves into the repercussions of being raised by dysfunctional and emotionally unavailable parents, and the ways addiction can take over ones life. <br /><br />At times this book is utterly heartwrenching and shocking. The author has a clear voice and is able to portray the perils of addiction in a realistic and vivid way. And yet at the same time, the tale of despair surrounding the protagonist's childhood and subsequent life as an addict is beautifully balanced within the narrative through the careful and considered incorporation of amazingly descriptive and life affirming scenes, which demonstrate how important love is and how even the tiniest bit of hope can help change a person's life. <br /><br />An amazing book from debut author JA Wright!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4679369101087781516" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


